No. M-1. An act relating to approval of amendments to the charter of the
City of Barre.
(H.10)
It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
Sec. 1. CHARTER AMENDMENT APPROVAL
The General Assembly approves the amendments to the charter of the City
of Barre as set forth in this act. The voters of the City approved the
amendments on May 14, 2024.
Sec. 2. 24 App. V.S.A. chapter 1 is amended to read:
CHAPTER 1. CITY OF BARRE
* * *
§ 110. FISCAL YEAR
The fiscal year of the City and the City School District shall begin on the
first day of July and end on the last day of June of each calendar year. The
fiscal year shall constitute the budget and accounting year as used in this
charter.
§ 111. BONDING OF CITY OFFICIALS
The Mayor, councilors, members of the Police Department, City Manager,
Finance Director, Superintendent of Public Works, Tax Collector, and Clerk,
and Treasurer shall annually be bonded by the City for the faithful discharge of
their respective duties, as provided by State statute, and the expense of said
bonds to be paid by the City.
* * *
